  levelNumber: 20
  levelName: Temple of the Masks
  location: "Pet\xE9n, Guatemala"
  levelDescription: "Painted faces of gods and ancestors watched over Yaxha from
    the Temple of the Masks.\n\nThe Temple of the Masks is part of the Yaxha archaeological
    site in Pet\xE9n, Guatemala. Built during the Late Classic period (c. 600\u2013800
    AD), it is named for the large stucco masks that decorate its facade. These masks
    represent deities and ancestral figures, symbolizing the Maya belief in the connection
    between rulers, gods, and the natural world.\r\n\r\nThe temple rises on the eastern
    side of the main plaza, facing its twin pyramid across the square. This layout
    reflects the Maya tradition of astronomical alignment, where paired structures
    marked solstices and ceremonial cycles. The masks themselves\u2014stylized faces
    with headdresses\u2014were painted in vivid colors, bringing the temple to life
    during rituals.\r\n\r\nToday, the Temple of the Masks stands as one of Yaxha\u2019s
    most iconic monuments, offering a glimpse into the artistry and spiritual symbolism
    of the ancient Maya."
  siteImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: bc3f9c10ed79fa2459ba15ad4e80c65b, type: 3}
